## Logging
Always use `src.proj.log.Logger` вЂ” never `print()` or stdlib `logging` directly.

## Path conventions
- **Never hardcode paths.** Use `PATH.xxx` from `src.proj.env.path`.
- All paths derive from `MACHINE.data_root` (set in machine config).

## Data and factors
- Correctness first; re-verify when changing data paths or transforms.
- Prefer vectorization and torch/polars when it clearly pays off; otherwise pandas.
- Data access: use `DateDataAccess` singletons (`TRADE`, `BS`, `MKLINE`, вЂ¦) or `DataAPI`.
- Raw data I/O: `src.proj.db` (`df_io.save`, `df_io.load`) вЂ” feather/parquet format.
- Factors: follow patterns under `src.res.factor` вЂ” subclass `FactorCalculator`, implement `calculate(data: DataBlock) -> DataBlock`. Auto-registered by metaclass.
- Respect existing cleaning choices: forward-fill в†’ winsorize в†’ industry neutralize в†’ z-score.
- Point-in-time discipline for fundamental data: use `BS.qtr()` / `BS.ttm()`, never period-end raw values.

## Model training
- Entry: `ModelAPI.schedule_model(schedule_name)` вЂ” schedule configs live in `configs/model/schedule/`.
- Do not instantiate NN/boost classes directly; go through `AlgoModule` / `ModelAPI`.
- New architectures: subclass `BaseNNModel` in `src/res/algo/nn/`, implement `forward(batch: BatchInput)` вЂ” auto-registered by class name.

## Backtesting and strategies
- Model all trading costs: commission, slippage, stamp duty, suspension limits.
- No lookahead: only information available at decision time.

## Script conventions
Every file in `scripts/` must have a YAML header block (lines starting with `#`, terminated by a blank line) that is parseable by `ScriptHeader.read_from_file()`:
```python
# coding: utf-8
# author: ...
# date: YYYY-MM-DD
# description: Short title
# content: Longer description
# email: True | False
# mode: shell | os
# parameters:
#   param_name:
#       type: str | int | float | bool | [opt1, opt2] | Options.available_xxx()
#       desc: explanation
#       required: True | False
#       default: value
```
Wrap `main()` with `@ScriptTool(task_name)` for task tracking, locking, and email.

## Interactive app
- Start: `uv run launch.py`
- Scripts visible to the app: numbered folders only (files/dirs starting with `.` or `_` are hidden).
- `Options.available_xxx()` methods provide dynamic dropdowns from the `options_cache.json`.

## Context library
Full module documentation is in `context/`. See `context/CLAUDE.md` for the index.
When a doc is found to be wrong, add `<!-- STALE: reason -->` inline and run:
```bash
uv run scripts/0_check/2_update_context.py --mode stale
```

## Data fetching policy
Ask the human before any new external scrape or introducing a new data provider.

## Repository hygiene
Do not suggest committing paths under `.local_resources/` or `.secret/` to git.

## Post-edit checks (substantive code changes)
```bash
ruff check src scripts
